N.33-33’W., 43.40 m. to point 11;

N.8-33’E., 85.30 m. to point 12;

N.17-21’E., 1.70 m. to point 13;

N.18-02’W., 73.30 m. to point of beginning, containing an area of SIXTY THOUSAND (60,000) SQUARE METERS, more or less. All points referred to are indicated on the plan and are marked on the ground by B.L. PS. cyl., conc. mons. except points 9, 11, and 12 by GI Spike; bearings true; date of original survey, April 20, 1906 – June 30, 1907 (Malinta Estate) and that of the relocation survey on March 7, 1956 by virtue of the Director of Lands.

The portion or portions of the areas herein declared open to disposition as are presently used or earmarked for public or quasi-public purposes shall be excluded from such disposition, except in favor of the Government or any of its branches or agencies. All land disposed of under this Proclamation shall not be subject to alienation for a term of ten (10) years from the issuance of the title, in case of sale, or execution of the contract, in case of lease, nor shall they become liable for the satisfaction of any debt contracted prior to the expiration of the said period; but that the same, together with the improvements thereon, may be mortgaged.

The housing project referred to herein shall be administered by the Department of Agriculture and, for this purpose, the National Housing Authority and other government instrumentalities involved in the Housing Program of the Government shall provide assistance in the disposition of homelots to qualified officials and employees of the Department of Agriculture and its offices, bureaus, agencies and attached corporations.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, I have hereunto set my hand and caused the seal of the Republic of the Philippines to be affixed.

DONE in the City of Manila, this 8th day of September in the year of Our Lord, two thousand.

(Sgd.) JOSEPH EJERCITO ESTRADA

By the President: (Sgd.) RONALDO B. ZAMORA Executive Secretary

